<li class="service-links-stumbleupon"><a href="http://www.stumbleupon.com/submit?url=http%3A%2F%2Fknowledgelayer.softlayer.com%2Farticles%2Fcloudlayer-computing-instance-cci-topic-description&amp;title=CloudLayer+Computing+Instance+%28CCI%29+Topic+Description" title="Thumb this up at StumbleUpon" class="service-links-stumbleupon" rel="nofollow"><img src="/sites/all/modules/service_links/images/stumbleit.png" alt="StumbleUpon" title="" width="16" height="16" /></a></li>
<li class="service-links-twitter last"><a href="http://twitter.com/share?url=http%3A%2F%2Fknowledgelayer.softlayer.com%2Farticles%2Fcloudlayer-computing-instance-cci-topic-description&amp;text=CloudLayer%20Computing%20Instance%20%28CCI%29%20Topic%20Description" title="Share this on Twitter" class="service-links-twitter" rel="nofollow"><img src="/sites/all/modules/service_links/images/twitter.png" alt="Twitter" title="" width="16" height="16" /></a></li>
</ul></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-body">
                <div class="field-content">CloudLayer Computing Instances (CCIs) are scalable virtual servers that may be purchased on either a monthly or hourly basis. They are a great option for customers looking to add additional resources in a virtual environment and are provisioned in a fraction of the time of physical devices. SoftLayer CCIs are fully customizable and can be ordered as public, private and bare metal cloud instances.</div>
  </div>
  
